The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           IN THE CITY
                  
	Mumbai took a vital first-innings lead over Bengal in the CK Nayudu Trophy semi-final at the Eden on Sunday. Murtuza Hussain (4/61) and Iqbal Abdullah (3/42) wrecked the Bengal batting as the hosts were restricted to 206 in their first innings.      
	SUMMARISED SCORES      
	At Eden: Mumbai 353 amp; 106/6 vs Bengal 206 (M. Hussain 4/61, Iqbal Abdullah (3/42).      
	 At Salt Lake: Punjab 249 amp; 145/7 vs Baroda 339/9 decl. (M. Baloch 150).          
	 Robson School of Cricket beat Barun Barman CA by one run in the Ambar Roy sub-junior cricket tournament at Sonarpur on Sunday.      
	SUMMARISED SCORES      
	Uttar Palli Milan Sangha CCC 144 vs Ashoke Sangha CA 145/6. Ashoke Sangha CA won by 6 wkts.      
	Howrah Union CCC 261 vs Barsat Association 178. Howrah Union won by 83 runs.          
	 1923 Chhatra Samity beat Rakhi Sangha 45-41 in the inaugural match of the 28th Senior Basketball championship at the West Bengal Basketball Association ground on Sunday.                
	FOOTBALL: Fed Cup  JCT vs ND Heroes from 3.30pm followed by East Bengal vs Sporting Clube de Goa. Both matches at Barasat Stadium.      
	CRICKET: CK Nayudu Trophy  Bengal vs Mumbai at the Eden; Punjab vs Baroda at JU ground in Salt Lake. Both from 9a.m.      
	BASKETBALL: 28th Senior championship at the WBBA ground from 7a.m.                                                                                                                                                                     
